<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <title>Old Fashion Recipe</title>
    </head>

<body>
    <header>
        <section>
            <img src="Old-Fashioned-Recipe-5-1.jpg" alt="Old Fashion">
            <h2>Why an Old Fashion</h2>
            <p>An Old Fashion is considered one the first, if not the first cocktail. It is incredibly simple to make.</p>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p>Traditionally, an Old Fashion is made with 3 key ingrediants; bourbon, simple Syrup and bitters.</p>
            <p>The recipe below is designed to act as a guide, and not something to be followed prescriptively. Play with your
                cocktail! Adjust the ingrediants or add new ones to compliment your taste.</p>
        </section>
    </header>
    <article>
        <section id="ingredients">
            <h3>Ingredients</h3>
            <ul>
                <li><a href="https://www.buffalotracedistillery.com/our-brands/buffalo-trace.html">50 ml of Buffalo Trace Bourbon</a></li>
                <li>12.5 ml of simple syrup</li>
                <li>2 dashes of <a href="https://angosturabitters.com/portfolio/orange-bitters/">Orange Angostura Bitters</a></li>
                <li>1 large ice cube</li>
                <li>1 <a href="https://www.luxardo.it/liqueurs-and-distillates/original-maraschino-cherries/">Luxardo Cherry</a></li>
                <li>1 <em>fresh</em> orange peele</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h3>Instructions</h3>
            <ol>
                <li>Put your large ice cube in low ball glass</li>
                <li>Measure out your spirits and pour directly into the glass</li>
                <li>Add your bitters</li>
                <li>Stir until chilled</li>
                <li>Add your garnishes</li>
                <li>Enjoy!</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </article>
    <footer><p>Government warning: (1) According to the Surgeon General, women should not drink alcoholic beverages during pregnancy because of the risk of birth defects. (2) Consumption of alcoholic beverage impairs your ability to drive a car or operate machinery, and may cause health problems. Drink responsibly.</p>
    </footer>
</body>

